text: Zhuquan Town () is a town and the county seat in the south western Jiahe County, Hunan, China. The town was reformed through the amalgamation of Panjiang Township () and 12 villages of the former Zhuquan Town on November 27, 2015. It has an area of with a population of 107,000 (as of 2015 end), its seat is at North Renmin Rd.
